---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="BeaconGuard Assurance">
  <!-- ===================== -->
  <!-- HERO -->
  <!-- ===================== -->
  <section class="landing">
    <h1>BeaconGuard Assurance</h1>

    <h2>
      Deterministic Control Plane for Regulated AI
    </h2>

   <center> <p>
      An authorization and audit layer that governs AI
      interactions in healthcare and other regulated environments.
    </p>

    <p>
      Policy-driven enforcement converts probabilistic model behavior into
      deterministic, auditable decisions.
    </p> </center>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== -->
  <!-- SYSTEM OVERVIEW -->
  <!-- ===================== -->
  <section>
    <h2>What BeaconGuard Is</h2>

    <p>
      BeaconGuard operates as an externalized control plane that sits between
      regulated systems and AI models.
    </p>

    <p>
      Authorization logic is removed from applications and enforced independently
      using signed, versioned policy artifacts.
    </p>

    <p>
      Every authorization decision produces an immutable audit record that can be
      replayed to prove why access was allowed or denied.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== -->
  <!-- PROBLEM -->
  <!-- ===================== -->
  <section>
    <h2>Why AI Authorization Fails Today</h2>

    <p>
      Most AI systems rely on application-level logging that records prompts,
      responses, and metadata but does not capture the authorization intent that
      governed the interaction.
    </p>

    <p>
      As models change and prompts evolve, historical logs lose the ability to
      explain why a decision occurred at a specific point in time.
    </p>

    <p>
      When authorization intent cannot be reconstructed deterministically,
      compliance review becomes speculative instead of evidentiary.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== -->
  <!-- DIFFERENTIATORS -->
  <!-- ===================== -->
  <section>
    <h2>What the BeaconGuard Policy Stack Changes</h2>

    <p>
      <strong>Deterministic Policy Evaluation.</strong>
      Decisions are evaluated against immutable policy snapshots that can be
      replayed to produce identical outcomes under identical inputs.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Externalized Enforcement.</strong>
      Authorization logic is enforced outside of applications and AI systems,
      independent of model internals or vendor implementations.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>First-Class Decision Audit.</strong>
      Each decision produces a verifiable record capturing policy identity,
      decision context, and outcome.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== -->
  <!-- CTA -->
  <!-- ===================== -->
  <section>
    <h2>Learn More</h2>

    <p>
      BeaconGuard is designed for regulated environments that require provable
      authorization guarantees, deterministic replay, and audit-ready evidence.
    </p>

    <p>
      Technical documentation will describe the control plane, enforcement
      runtime, and audit model in detail.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>